Problem statement
Aryan and his friends are very fond of the pattern. For a given integer ‘N’, they want to make the Reverse N-Number Triangle.

Example:
Input: ‘N’ = 3

Output: 

1 2 3
1 2
1

void nNumberTriangle(int n) {
	for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
          for (int j = 0; j < n - i + 1; j++) {
            printf("%d ", j+1);
          }
          printf("\n");
        }
    
}
